---
// PlanFlipRace — Chapter 072 Lesson 2, "Picking the right invalidation call".
//
// The post-purchase plan-flip case: the user lands on the success page while the
// Stripe webhook is still in flight, so the two events race. The figure makes the
// race legible across four scrubbed steps so the student can *see* the lesson's
// top misconception dismantled — router.refresh() re-renders but never expires a
// cached read; it is the webhook's revalidateTag that marks it stale, and a later
// refresh that finally observes the fresh value.
//
// Layout: two fixed lanes side by side — "Browser / success page" and "Stripe
// webhook" — with a shared "Cached entitlement" state pill spanning beneath them.
// Each step lights the active lane, animates the action (a self-loop arrow for a
// poll, a downward arrow when the webhook writes), and recolours the pill. The
// lane geometry is identical in every step so only state changes as the reader
// scrubs — the diagram-sequence stage sizes to the tallest step and never reflows.
//
// Colour language is shared with TwoAxisGrid in this folder: the cache states use
// a neutral→amber→green progression (Free = neutral, Stale = amber, Pro = green),
// and "router.refresh()" is consistently marked as a re-render, never an
// invalidation, so steps 2 and 4 read as "same call, different outcome".
//
// Engine: plain HTML + CSS inside DiagramStep bodies — the diagrams index's pick
// for a sequential phase strip rendered with real CSS. Each <DiagramStep> is a
// direct child of <DiagramSequence> (the component finds them via [data-ds-step]).

import DiagramSequence from '../../../figures/diagram-sequence/DiagramSequence.astro';
import DiagramStep from '../../../figures/diagram-sequence/DiagramStep.astro';
---

<div class="pfr-scope">
	<DiagramSequence>
		{/* ── Step 1 — redirect lands, webhook not yet here, cache says Free ───── */}
		<DiagramStep>
			<div class="pfr-scene">
				<div class="pfr-lanes">
					<div class="pfr-lane is-active" data-lane="browser">
						<span class="pfr-lane-title">Browser / success page</span>
						<div class="pfr-card is-arriving">
							<span class="pfr-card-label">redirected from Checkout</span>
							<span class="pfr-card-state">success page mounting</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="pfr-lane is-idle" data-lane="webhook">
						<span class="pfr-lane-title">Stripe webhook</span>
						<div class="pfr-card is-ghost">
							<span class="pfr-card-state">not arrived yet</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="pfr-pill" data-state="free">
					<span class="pfr-pill-label">Cached entitlement</span>
					<span class="pfr-pill-value">Free</span>
				</div>
			</div>
			<Fragment slot="caption">
				Checkout completes. The browser is redirected to the success page; the webhook has not arrived yet. The cached entitlement read still says <strong>Free</strong>.
			</Fragment>
		</DiagramStep>

		{/* ── Step 2 — first router.refresh(): re-renders, still Free ─────────── */}
		<DiagramStep>
			<div class="pfr-scene">
				<div class="pfr-lanes">
					<div class="pfr-lane is-active" data-lane="browser">
						<span class="pfr-lane-title">Browser / success page</span>
						<div class="pfr-card">
							<span class="pfr-card-label">renders "Activating…"</span>
							<code class="pfr-card-call">router.refresh()</code>
							<span class="pfr-loop" aria-hidden="true">↻ poll</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="pfr-lane is-idle" data-lane="webhook">
						<span class="pfr-lane-title">Stripe webhook</span>
						<div class="pfr-card is-ghost">
							<span class="pfr-card-state">still in flight</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="pfr-pill" data-state="free">
					<span class="pfr-pill-label">Cached entitlement</span>
					<span class="pfr-pill-value">Free</span>
					<span class="pfr-pill-note">re-rendered, not invalidated</span>
				</div>
			</div>
			<Fragment slot="caption">
				The success page mounts, renders "Activating…", and fires its first <code>router.refresh()</code>. The server render re-runs &mdash; but the cached read is still valid, so it still says <strong>Free</strong>. The refresh re-rendered; it did not invalidate.
			</Fragment>
		</DiagramStep>

		{/* ── Step 3 — webhook lands, writes, calls revalidateTag → Stale ─────── */}
		<DiagramStep>
			<div class="pfr-scene">
				<div class="pfr-lanes">
					<div class="pfr-lane is-idle" data-lane="browser">
						<span class="pfr-lane-title">Browser / success page</span>
						<div class="pfr-card is-ghost">
							<span class="pfr-card-state">waiting on the poll</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="pfr-lane is-active" data-lane="webhook">
						<span class="pfr-lane-title">Stripe webhook</span>
						<div class="pfr-card">
							<span class="pfr-card-label">writes entitlement row</span>
							<code class="pfr-card-call">revalidateTag(…, 'max')</code>
							<span class="pfr-arrow" aria-hidden="true">↓ invalidates</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="pfr-pill" data-state="stale">
					<span class="pfr-pill-label">Cached entitlement</span>
					<span class="pfr-pill-value">Stale</span>
					<span class="pfr-pill-note">was Free</span>
				</div>
			</div>
			<Fragment slot="caption">
				The webhook lands. The handler writes the entitlement row and calls <code>revalidateTag(orgTags.all(orgId), 'max')</code>. Now the cached read is <strong>stale</strong>.
			</Fragment>
		</DiagramStep>

		{/* ── Step 4 — next router.refresh() observes the recompute → Pro ─────── */}
		<DiagramStep>
			<div class="pfr-scene">
				<div class="pfr-lanes">
					<div class="pfr-lane is-active is-resolved" data-lane="browser">
						<span class="pfr-lane-title">Browser / success page</span>
						<div class="pfr-card">
							<span class="pfr-card-label">poll stops</span>
							<code class="pfr-card-call">router.refresh()</code>
							<span class="pfr-loop is-done" aria-hidden="true">✓ shows Pro</span>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="pfr-lane is-idle" data-lane="webhook">
						<span class="pfr-lane-title">Stripe webhook</span>
						<div class="pfr-card is-ghost">
							<span class="pfr-card-state">done</span>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="pfr-pill is-resolved" data-state="pro">
					<span class="pfr-pill-label">Cached entitlement</span>
					<span class="pfr-pill-value">Pro</span>
					<span class="pfr-pill-note">stale read recomputed</span>
				</div>
			</div>
			<Fragment slot="caption">
				The next <code>router.refresh()</code> re-runs the server render. This time the stale read recomputes and the page shows <strong>Pro</strong>. The poll stops.
			</Fragment>
		</DiagramStep>
	</DiagramSequence>
</div>

<style>
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-scene) {
		box-sizing: border-box;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 14px;
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 640px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 4px 0 2px;
		font-family: var(--sl-font-system, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, sans-serif);
	}
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-scene *) {
		box-sizing: border-box;
		margin: 0;
	}

	/* ── Two lanes side by side ──────────────────────────────────────────── */
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-lanes) {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 12px;
	}
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-lane) {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
		padding: 10px 10px 12px;
		border-radius: 12px;
		border: 1.5px solid var(--sl-color-hairline, #d0d5dd);
		background: var(--sl-color-bg, #fff);
		transition: none;
	}
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-lane.is-idle) {
		opacity: 0.55;
	}
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-lane.is-active[data-lane='browser']) {
		--pfr-accent: #7c3aed;
		border-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--pfr-accent) 55%, var(--sl-color-hairline));
		background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--pfr-accent) 8%, var(--sl-color-bg));
	}
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-lane.is-active[data-lane='webhook']) {
		--pfr-accent: #0d9488;
		border-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--pfr-accent) 55%, var(--sl-color-hairline));
		background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--pfr-accent) 8%, var(--sl-color-bg));
	}
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-lane.is-resolved[data-lane='browser']) {
		--pfr-accent: #16a34a;
		border-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--pfr-accent) 58%, var(--sl-color-hairline));
		background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--pfr-accent) 9%, var(--sl-color-bg));
	}
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-lane-title) {
		font-size: 11px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 0.02em;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-2, #475569);
	}

	/* ── The action card inside each lane ────────────────────────────────── */
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-card) {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 4px;
		padding: 10px 11px;
		border-radius: 10px;
		border: 1.5px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--pfr-accent, #94a3b8) 40%, var(--sl-color-hairline));
		background: var(--sl-color-bg, #fff);
		min-height: 76px;
		justify-content: center;
	}
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-card.is-arriving) {
		border-style: solid;
		box-shadow: 0 2px 0 0 color-mix(in srgb, var(--pfr-accent) 35%, transparent);
	}
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-card.is-ghost) {
		border-style: dashed;
		border-color: var(--sl-color-gray-5, #d0d5dd);
		background: transparent;
		min-height: 76px;
	}
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-card-label) {
		font-size: 11.5px;
		font-weight: 600;
		line-height: 1.3;
		color: var(--sl-color-white, #1e293b);
	}
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-card-state) {
		font-size: 11px;
		font-style: italic;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #64748b);
	}
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-card-call) {
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, Monaco, Consolas, monospace;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 700;
		line-height: 1.25;
		color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--pfr-accent, #475569) 26%, var(--sl-color-white));
		word-break: break-word;
	}
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-loop),
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-arrow) {
		font-size: 10.5px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 0.02em;
		color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--pfr-accent, #64748b) 35%, var(--sl-color-white));
	}
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-loop.is-done) {
		color: #16a34a;
	}

	/* ── The shared cache-state pill ─────────────────────────────────────── */
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-pill) {
		display: flex;
		align-items: baseline;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 6px 10px;
		padding: 9px 14px;
		border-radius: 999px;
		border: 1.5px solid var(--pfr-pill-accent, #94a3b8);
		background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--pfr-pill-accent, #94a3b8) 12%, var(--sl-color-bg));
	}
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-pill[data-state='free']) {
		--pfr-pill-accent: #94a3b8;
	}
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-pill[data-state='stale']) {
		--pfr-pill-accent: #d97706;
	}
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-pill[data-state='pro']) {
		--pfr-pill-accent: #16a34a;
	}
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-pill-label) {
		font-size: 10.5px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 0.04em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-2, #475569);
	}
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-pill-value) {
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 800;
		color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--pfr-pill-accent) 30%, var(--sl-color-white));
	}
	.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-pill-note) {
		font-size: 10.5px;
		font-style: italic;
		color: var(--sl-color-gray-3, #64748b);
	}

	/* ── Narrow viewports: stack the lanes ───────────────────────────────── */
	@media (max-width: 460px) {
		.pfr-scope :global(.pfr-lanes) {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
